{"cursor":"6204","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nAn Individual's 'status' is a legal position held in regards to the rest of the\ncommunity and not by an act of law or by the consensual acts of the parties,\nand it is [[in rem]], i.e. these conditions must be recognised by the world. It\nis the qualities of universality and permanence that distinguish status from\nconsensual relationships such as employment and agency. Hence, a person's\nstatus and its attributes are set by the law of the domicile if born in a\ncommon law state, or by the law of nationality if born in a civil law state and\nthis status and its attendant capacities should be recognised wherever the\nperson may later travel.\n","linknr":190,"url":"Legal_status","recorded":1362676786,"links":18,"instances":["outcaste","conflict","conflict","legal","law","legal_system","area","law","law","business","law","law","law","law"],"pdf":[],"categories":["International law","Conflict of laws"],"headings":["Identity/personality","Personal status","Footnotes"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["party","law"],["agency","law"],["domicile","law"],["jurisdiction","area"],["civil_law","legal_system"],["capacity","law"],["dalit","outcaste"],["minor","law"],["capacity","law"],["marriage","conflict"],["contract","conflict"],["incorporation","business"],["public_policy","law"],["minor","law"],["legitimacy","law"],["ward","legal"]],"members":["dalit","contract","marriage","ward","minor","civil_law","jurisdiction","capacity","party","incorporation","public_policy","legitimacy","agency","domicile"],"related":["Law","Consent","Party_(law)","Employment","Agency_(law)","Domicile_(law)","Common_law","Jur